The paper presents a framework that uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to automatically detect and localize tumors in gigapixel microscopy images. This involves image analysis, computer vision, and machine learning techniques, which are all relevant to the computer science subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of CNNs also suggests that the paper may fall under the subfields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and deep learning (cs.DL). Finally, the paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) in terms of detecting and localizing specific features within large datasets.
